<paragraph id="904ADB69CBF26563B342177419A67208" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">The type material at B was destroyed during World War II. I am selecting as the lectotype the duplicate preserved at US that I have studied. I have also seen the duplicate at G, but have not carefully studied it.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="81745742BE29C09E49E58179DCCE1E6B" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">
Correspondence with Irina Illarionova and Vladimir Dorofeyev (LE) resulted in no specimen from the Chamisso herbarium collected by Sellow for 
<taxonomicName id="F010039687884205B208A150FB4CDF35" class="Insecta" family="Cordiaceae" genus="Cordia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cordia multispicata" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multispicata">
<emphasis id="B043D133AAE8F004D3DAE75C1B3A08F7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Cordia multispicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="012F4D8F63DB25C04596BBF001548829" authorityName="A. Borhidi" authorityYear="1988" baseAuthorityName="Cham." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Varronia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Varronia multispicata" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multispicata">
<emphasis id="7623E4FAFEA94C09DD8249EECC45CF24" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Varronia multispicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the LE collections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0FE98541ABB50FC95D284CFB6B065F35" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">
